  "prompt": "I'm 5'2 and 130 pounds. I've dealt with body issues all my life and tried losing weight the past month with no changes. What can I do?",
  "response": "Here are some suggestions to help you with weight loss and body image:\n\n1. Diet Tips:\n- Track calorie intake using apps like MyFitnessPal\n- Focus on whole foods, lean proteins, fruits, and vegetables\n- Reduce processed foods and sugar\n- Stay hydrated\n- Consider consulting a nutritionist\n\n2. Exercise Recommendations:\n- Combine cardio and strength training\n- Start with 30 minutes of exercise 3-4 times a week\n- Try HIIT (High-Intensity Interval Training)\n- Include weight lifting to build muscle\n- Find activities you enjoy\n\n3. Mental Health Strategies:\n- Practice positive self-talk\n- Set realistic goals\n- Consider therapy for body image issues\n- Don't focus solely on the scale\n- Measure progress by fitness improvements\n\n4. Additional Suggestions:\n- Get enough sleep (7-9 hours)\n- Manage stress\n- Be patient with yourself\n- Consider consulting a doctor to rule out any underlying health issues\n\n5. Body Composition Tips:\n- At 5'2\", 130 pounds is within a healthy BMI range\n- Focus on body composition over pure weight loss\n- Build muscle to increase metabolism\n\nRemember, sustainable lifestyle changes are more important than quick fixes.",
